Package dk.jakobhandersen.multiregionexporterforcubase

Class AudioBite

java.lang.Object
dk.jakobhandersen.multiregionexporterforcubase.AudioBite
public class AudioBite
extends java.lang.Object
Class that represents one audio region that is to be copied from the full file to its own file.
Author:
Jakob Hougaard Andersen.

  • Field Details

    • startValue

      private double startValue
      Start time value. Note that the value can be described in different time formats (TimeFormat) defined in startValueFormat.

    • startValueFormat

      private TimeFormat startValueFormat
      The time format of the startValue variable

    • lengthValue

      private double lengthValue
      Length value. Note that the value can be described in different time formats (TimeFormat) defined in lengthValueFormat.

    • lengthValueFormat

      private TimeFormat lengthValueFormat
      The time format of the lengthValue variable

    • startSec

      private double startSec
      Start time in seconds. Calculated from startValue.

    • endSec

      private double endSec
      End time in seconds. Calculated from startValue and lengthValue.

    • functionalEndSec

      private double functionalEndSec
      The actually used value in seconds for end when creating audio files and range markers. This value includes trailing time and is clamped to audio file length.

    • name

      private java.lang.String name
      The name of the AudioBite. Will also be the filename (without file ending).

    • nameSetNormally

      private boolean nameSetNormally
      Indicates whether the name has been set normally (from element description/name). This is used to determine whether it is allowed to override name with audio file name (fall-back if no name/description).

    • startValueSet

      private boolean startValueSet
      Has the start value been set?

    • lengthValueSet

      private boolean lengthValueSet
      Has the length value been set?

    • startAndEndSecCalculated

      private boolean startAndEndSecCalculated
      Has the start and end time in seconds been calculated ?

    • functionalEndSet

      private boolean functionalEndSet
      Has functionalEnd been set?
